  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3, W-EP-04)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 3. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. Of the 13 credibility factors, 10 are assessed (several with achieved levels below required levels) and 3 are flagged as not-assessed on grounds that they were considered beyond the scope of the current submission cycle. Given MRL 3, these unassessed factors materially weaken overall credibility, though the decision record characterises the gaps as minor. Decision: Accepted.",
